<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06105181 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06105181 </ACCESS><CAPTION>  Photo; PHOTO: Cher played Streep's lover in 'Silkwood'  </CAPTION><DESCRIPT>  MOVIE; LIST; IMAGE; HOMOSEXUAL; MEN; WOMEN  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  (box) &quot;Silkwood&quot;: Mike Nichols' 1983 drama about a nuclear-plantwhistle-blower features Cher in a matter-of-fact portrayal of Meryl Streep'slesbian roommate.;    (box) &quot;Internal Affairs&quot;: This 1989 cop movie includes apolicewoman who happens to be a lesbian.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Arts andamp; Books  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  FILMS THAT SHOWED POSITIVE IMAGES  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     (box) &quot;Victor-Victoria&quot;: Despite the drag-queen setting, this 1982 comedybusts at least one stereotype by having macho ex-football player Alex Karrasfall for Robert Preston's more flamboyant gay character.;    (box) &quot;DesertHearts&quot;: By no means a mainstream picture, this 1986 drama is considered ahallmark film in its frank and poignant depiction of lesbian characters.;   (box) &quot;Longtime Companion&quot;: This 1990 movie was the first to dealintelligently with the effect of the AIDS crisis on New York's upscale gaycommunity. Bruce Davison was nominated for an Oscar as best-supporting actor(but lost to Joe Pesci of &quot;GoodFellas.&quot;).;    (box) &quot;Kiss of the SpiderWoman&quot;: Hector Babenco's 1985 drama is a special case. Released by FilmDallas,it was a non-Hollywood production with a foreign director. The movie's profilewas raised when William Hurt won an Oscar for his performance. While thesubstance of the gay character he played was positive, it also reinforced astereotype in that the character was an effeminate female impersonator.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Dallas Morning News  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910414  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Sunday  </DAY><MONTH>  April  </MONTH><PG.COL>  3  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><FEATURE>  PHOTO  </FEATURE><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  216  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Sunday April 14, 199100105181,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>